WHAT IS THIS FILE
The certified computing profile for the Intel Core Ultra 9 285H mobile
processor, based on the Arrow Lake architecture. It defines the hybrid
CPU cluster (Lion Cove P-cores + Skymont E-cores), Intel Arc GPU (8 Xe
cores), and the AI Boost NPU with 13 TOPS (INT8) throughput.

WHY IT EXISTS
Arrow Lake introduces a disaggregated tile design with Foveros 3D
packaging, combining TSMC N3B (CPU), N5/N6 (GPU/IO) processes. GIOP
models this as formulas so that AI-accelerated grading, rendering, and
video encoding/decoding times are predictable on Intel-powered mobile
workstations.

HOW IT WORKS
CPU Performance (Hybrid):
  P_cores = 6 Lion Cove at up to 5.4 GHz (P-core)
  E_cores = 8 Skymont at up to 4.5 GHz (E-core)
  Low-power E-cores = 2 Skymont at up to 2.5 GHz (LP-E)
  Multi-core throughput:
    Perf_total = Σ (Perf_core_i * utilization_i)
    where Perf_core_i ∝ IPC_i * f_i. IPC Lion Cove ≈ 1.13× Raptor Cove.
  Total platform TOPS (CPU+GPU+NPU) up to 99.[reference:16][reference:17]

NPU AI Boost (INT8):
  TOPS_INT8 = 13 (dedicated NPU). Additional GPU compute: ~12 TOPS (Xe).
  Combined AI throughput ≈ 36 TOPS.[reference:18]

GPU (Intel Arc, 8 Xe cores):
  TFLOPS_FP16 = (Xe_cores * EUs_per_Xe * 2 * f_gpu) / 1e12
  = (8 * 16 * 2 * 2.35e9) / 1e12 ≈ 4.8 TFLOPS
  Supports DirectML, OpenVINO, ONNX RT, WebNN for AI inference.[reference:19]

Memory Bandwidth (LPDDR5x-8400):
  BW = bus_width_bytes * f_data * 2 (DDR)
  = 16 * 8.4e9 * 2 = 268.8 GB/s

Power:
  Base TDP: 45 W (configurable up to 115 W turbo). The runtime monitors
  CPU/GPU/NPU power domains and throttles independently.

WHERE IT IS DEPLOYED
- High-performance laptops (Dell XPS 17, Lenovo ThinkPad X1 Extreme).
- GIOP mobile grading workstations, on-set DIT carts, real-time AI
  noise reduction.

WHO USES IT
L2 Engineers deploying GIOP on Windows 11 laptops; L3 Colorists performing
on-set grades with AI assistance.

WHAT PROBLEM IT SOLVES
Models the Arrow Lake disaggregated tile architecture and its NPU as
formulas, enabling accurate prediction of AI-accelerated grading latency
and encoding throughput on Intel mobile platforms.

